PN,41802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1778785872
OL,3,CHampshire and Thames Valley police
OL,4,Ctrial world's first laughing gas
OL,5,Cbreathalyser
OL,7,FPossession of the class C drug for
OL,8,Funlawful use can lead to a prison
OL,9,Fsentence of up to two years.
OL,11,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,12,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,13,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,14,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,16,FA spokesman for the forces said:
OL,17,F"Driving under the influence of
OL,18,Fnitrous oxide is an emerging threat to
OL,19,Fthe safety of motorists on our roads.
OL,26,@yD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1778785872
OL,3,CHampshire and Thames Valley police
OL,4,Ctrial world's first laughing gas
OL,5,Cbreathalyser
OL,7,F"Its use can cause unconsciousness and
OL,8,Feven neurological damage or death from
OL,9,Fsuffocation of the oxygen supply to
OL,10,Fthe brain.
OL,12,F"Tragically, our officers have already
OL,13,Fseen deaths connected to drivers who
OL,14,Fwere under the influence of NOS.
OL,16,F"The innovative device is being tested
OL,17,Fby our officers to see if it can be
OL,18,Fused to detect if a driver is under
OL,19,Fthe influence of this harmful drug.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1778785872
OL,3,CHampshire and Thames Valley police
OL,4,Ctrial world's first laughing gas
OL,5,Cbreathalyser
OL,7,F"If successful, this could lead these
OL,8,Fmotorists to be prosecuted for drug
OL,9,Fdriving offences."
OL,11,FThe breathalyser, created by Respira
OL,12,FTechnologies following research at the
OL,13,FVrije Universiteit Amsterdam, works by
OL,14,Fthe user breathing into the portable
OL,15,Fdevice, with the result coming within
OL,16,Fminutes.
OL,18,FIt can detect whether a user has
OL,19,Finhaled nitrous oxide for up to two
OL,20,Fhours beforehand.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@RO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1778785872
OL,3,CHampshire and Thames Valley police
OL,4,Ctrial world's first laughing gas
OL,5,Cbreathalyser
OL,7,FActing Superintendent Emma Hart, of
OL,8,Fthe joint operations roads policing
OL,9,Funit of Hampshire & Isle of Wight
OL,10,FConstabulary and Thames Valley Police,
OL,11,Fsaid: "There is currently no device
OL,12,Favailable that can prove a driver
OL,13,Finhaled laughing gas, making
OL,14,Fprosecution difficult.
OL,16,F"That is why our forces are leading
OL,17,Fthis testing phase, to break new
OL,18,Fground and prove these devices can
OL,19,Fhelp save lives on our roads.
OL,26,@sD@GOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
